{"url": "https://www.ics.uci.edu/~eppstein/ca/b35s236/guns.html", "content": "<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD HTML 3.2//EN\">\n<html>\n<head>\n<title>B35/S236 Glider and Spaceship Guns</title>\n</head>\n<body bgcolor=\"#FFFFFF\" text=\"#000000\">\n<h1><a href=\"/~eppstein/ca/b35s236/\">B35/S236</a></h1>\n\n<h2>Glider and Spaceship Guns</h2>\n\nDean found a very simple gun based on two p68 oscillators: \n\n<div align=\"CENTER\"><a href=\"gun.lif\"><img src=\"gun.gif\" width=\"43\"\nheight=\"71\" alt=\"p68 gun\"></a></div>\n\n<p>The p68 can also eat gliders, or turn them 180 or 90\ndegrees:</p>\n\n<div align=\"CENTER\">\n<table cellpadding=\"15\">\n<tr align=\"CENTER\" valign=\"MIDDLE\">\n<td><a href=\"p68-eat.lif\"><img src=\"p68-eat.gif\" width=\"87\" height= \n\"23\" alt=\"p68 eater\"></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"p68-180.lif\"><img src=\"p68-180.gif\" width=\"91\" height= \n\"23\" alt=\"p68 mirror\"></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"p68-90.lif\"><img src=\"p68-90.gif\" width=\"83\" height=\n\"19\" alt=\"p68 turn\"></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n\n<p>The timing of p68 glider streams turns out to be quite\nconvenient for many reactions, but if the p68 gun is not thin\nenough, one can use these thinner guns:</p>\n\n<div align=\"CENTER\">\n<table cellpadding=\"15\">\n<tr align=\"CENTER\" valign=\"MIDDLE\">\n<td><a href=\"gun-136.lif\"><img src=\"gun-136.gif\" width=\"103\"\nheight=\"155\" alt=\"p136 gun\"></a></td>\n<td><a href=\"gun-272.lif\"><img src=\"gun-272.gif\" alt=\"p272 gun\"\nwidth=\"235\" height=\"175\"></a></td>\n</tr>\n</table>\n</div>\n\n<p>Perhaps the most versatile gun is one with period 408, allowing\nglider reactions to involve both p24 and p68 oscillators:</p>\n\n<div align=\"CENTER\"><a href=\"gun-408.lif\"><img src=\"gun-408.gif\"\nalt=\"p408 gun\" width=\"151\" height=\"183\"></a></div>\n\n<p>It is also possible, but more difficult, to base a gun on the\np24 oscillator alone. It seems likely that the following gun can be\nmodified to produce periods of the form 24*<i>k</i> for all\nsufficiently large values of <i>k</i>; the gun shown has <i>\nk</i>&nbsp;=&nbsp;9.</p>\n\n<div align=\"CENTER\"><a href=\"gun-216.lif\"><img src=\"gun-216.gif\"\nalt=\"p216 gun\" width=\"345\" height=\"279\"></a></div>\n\n<p>Three glider guns can be combined to form a 4c/10 spaceship\ngun:</p>\n\n<div align=\"CENTER\"><a href=\"4c10-factory.lif\"><img src= \n\"4c10-factory.gif\" width=\"215\" height=\"131\" alt=\n\"p68 4c/10 gun\"></a></div>\n\n<p>One can also use glider collisions to make a gun for the wide\n2c/5 spaceship</p>\n\n<div align=\"CENTER\"><a href=\"widebody-factory.lif\"><img src= \n\"widebody-factory.gif\" width=\"367\" height=\"335\" alt=\n\"p68 wide 2c/5 spaceship gun\"></a></div>\n\nand for the c/6 spaceship: \n\n<div align=\"CENTER\"><a href=\"c6-gun.lif\"><img src=\"c6-gun.gif\" alt=\n\"p136 c/6 spaceship gun\" width=\"633\" height=\"333\"></a></div>\n\n<hr>\n<p><a href=\"/~eppstein/ca/b35s236/\">B35/S236</a> -- <a href= \n\"/~eppstein/ca/\">Cellular Automata</a> -- <a href=\"/~eppstein/\">D.\nEppstein</a> -- <a href=\"/\">UCI Inf. &amp; Comp. Sci.</a></p>\n</body>\n</html>\n\n", "encoding": "ascii"}